  <section>
    <h2>Menu Separators</h2>
    <p>Use <code>role="separator"</code> on list items to create visual dividers in context menus.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Semantic Structure</h3>
    <p>The menu element conveys that its items are commands. Each <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> should contain a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> for proper interaction.</p>

    <h3>ARIA Roles</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>role="separator"</code> &mdash; Marks visual dividers between groups of items</li>
      <li><code>aria-label</code> &mdash; Required on icon-only buttons to describe the action</li>
      <li><code>aria-disabled</code> &mdash; For non-functional menu items</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Icon Buttons</h3>
    <p>When using icon-only buttons, always include an <code>aria-label</code> for screen reader users:</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Icon button with aria-label">{{ iconButtonCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Action</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Tab</kbd></td>
          <td>Move focus between menu buttons</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Enter</kbd> / <kbd>Space</kbd></td>
          <td>Activate focused button</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

